import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['normal'] = pd.to_numeric(data['normal'], errors='ignore')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='normal', kde=True)
    plt.xlabel('Normal Temperature')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of normal temperatures?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    else:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    data['record'] = pd.to_datetime(data['record'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    data['forecast'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecast'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    chart = sns.boxplot(x="variable", y="value", data=pd.melt(data[['normal', 'actual']]), palette="Set3")
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the difference between normal and actual temperatures?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['record'] = pd.to_datetime(data['record'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    data['actual'] = pd.to_numeric(data['actual'], errors='ignore')
    ax = sns.lineplot(x='record', y='actual', data=data)
    ax.set(xlabel='Record Date', ylabel='Actual Temperature')
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.title('What is the trend of actual temperatures over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
